    <h1 class="title">About CARS</h1>
    
    <div class="box">
        <h2 class="subtitle">What is CARS?</h2>
        <p>
            The Children and Adolescents Risk Screener (CARS) is a comprehensive assessment tool 
            designed to help identify students who may benefit from additional support services.
        </p>
        
        <h3 class="title is-4">Assessment Components</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Externalizing Behaviors:</strong> Acting out, defiance, attention issues</li>
            <li><strong>Internalizing Behaviors:</strong> Sadness, anxiety, withdrawal</li>
            <li><strong>Social Difficulties:</strong> Peer relationships, social skills</li>
            <li><strong>Academic/Learning Issues:</strong> School performance, engagement</li>
            <li><strong>Self-Harm Screening:</strong> Thoughts of hurting oneself</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3 class="title is-4">Risk Levels</h3>
        <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag is-success is-large">Normal/No Risk</span>
            <span class="tag is-warning is-large">At-Risk</span>
            <span class="tag is-danger is-large">High Risk</span>
        </div>
        
        <h3 class="title is-4">Support Tiers</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Tier I:</strong> Universal support for all students</li>
            <li><strong>Tier II:</strong> Targeted interventions for at-risk students</li>
            <li><strong>Tier III:</strong> Intensive support for high-risk students</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="notification is-warning">
        <h4 class="title is-5">Important Disclaimer</h4>
        <p>
            This tool is for educational and screening purposes only. It is not a substitute for 
            professional mental health assessment or diagnosis. If you or someone you know is 
            experiencing thoughts of self-harm, please seek immediate help from a trusted adult, 
            counselor, or mental health professional.
        </p>
    </div>
    
